  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb \u0dc4\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Six years of recovery",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "1990 Suvasarya Ambulance Service, which is engaged in a mission to expedite patient care for the development of health services, has completed six years.",
        "On the advice of President Ranil Wickramasinghe, the 1990 Suvasarya Ambulance Service was started on July 28, 2016 under the leadership of Member of Parliament Dr. Harsha De Silva.",
        "Its pilot project was started in Western and Southern provinces using 88 ambulances.",
        "For that, India made a non-repayable donation of 7.55 million dollars.",
        "Based on the success of this pilot project, India again donated $15.2 million to Sri Lanka to start this service islandwide.",
        "18 of 2018 No. 18 of 2018, the Suvasarya Foundation established by the Suvasarya Foundation Act of 1990 is currently managed entirely at the expense of the government.",
        "More than twelve lakh patients have been admitted to hospital by this service.",
        "Suvasarya Ambulance Service has received more than 54 lakh calls so far.",
        "The Board of Directors of Suvasarya including Mr. Dumindra Ratnayake, President of Suvasarya and its Chief Executive Officer Sohanda Silva have been leading its activities for five years."
      ],
